OL,6,FCoskun denies a religiously aggravated
OL,7,Fpublic order offence of using
OL,8,Fdisorderly behaviour "within the
OL,9,Fhearing or sight of a person likely to
OL,10,Fbe caused harassment, alarm or
OL,11,Fdistress", motivated by "hostility
OL,12,Ftowards members of a religious group,
OL,13,Fnamely followers of Islam", contrary
OL,14,Fto the Crime and Disorder Act 1998 and
OL,15,Fthe Public Order Act 1986.
