OL,6,FHe also pleaded not guilty to an
OL,7,Falternative charge of using disorderly
OL,8,Fbehaviour "within the hearing or sight
OL,9,Fof a person likely to be caused
OL,10,Fharassment, alarm or distress",
OL,11,Fcontrary to section five of the Public
OL,12,FOrder Act 1986.
OL,14,FThe charges are alternative to each
OL,15,Fother, meaning if hostility towards
OL,16,Freligion is not proven, Coskun could
OL,17,Fstill be found guilty of the simple
OL,18,Foffence of disorderly behaviour.
