OL,3,CJudge set to pass verdict after trial
OL,4,Cof man who burned Koran
OL,6,FHis lawyer, Katy Thorne KC, argued
OL,7,Flast week that the prosecution is
OL,8,Feffectively trying to revive blasphemy
OL,9,Flaws, which were abolished in England
OL,10,Fand Wales in 2008 and Scotland in 2021.
OL,12,FBlasphemy remains an offence in
OL,13,FNorthern Ireland but is rarely
OL,14,Fenforced.
OL,16,FProsecutor Philip McGhee said the case
OL,17,Fis about disorderly conduct, not the
OL,18,Fact of burning the Koran itself,
OL,19,Fadding that the prosecution of Coskun
OL,20,Fdoes not represent a restriction on
OL,21,Fcriticising religion.
