OL,6,FStephen Evans, chief executive of the
OL,7,FNSS, said before the trial: "A
OL,8,Fsuccessful prosecution in this case
OL,9,Fcould represent the effective
OL,10,Fcriminalisation of damaging a Koran in
OL,11,Fpublic, edging us dangerously close to
OL,12,Fa prohibition on blasphemy.
OL,14,F"The case also highlights the alarming
OL,15,Fuse of public order laws to curtail
OL,16,Four collective right to protest and
OL,17,Ffree speech based on the subjective
OL,18,Freactions of others.
